Hero MotoCorp and Harley-Davidson have announced the prices for the 2025 Harley-Davidson motorcycle lineup in India!

The 2025 lineup introduces a range of updates, including the launch of two premium Custom Vehicle Operations (CVO) models—CVO Street Glide and CVO Road Glide. These limited-production motorcycles feature new performance and design enhancements.

The Street Bob returns to the Indian market with a Milwaukee-Eight 117 engine, offering improved power and performance. However, the Fat Bob, a popular cruiser, has been discontinued and will no longer be part of the Indian lineup.

Here is the ex-showroom price list for the 2025 Harley-Davidson motorcycles in India:
-- H-D Nightster: ₹13,51,000
-- H-D Nightster Special: ₹14,29,000
-- H-D Sportster S: ₹16,70,000
-- H-D Pan America Special: ₹25,10,000
-- H-D Breakout: ₹37,19,000
-- H-D Fatboy: ₹25,90,000
-- H-D Heritage Classic: ₹23,85,000
-- H-D Street Glide: ₹39,29,999
-- H-D Road Glide: ₹42,30,000
-- H-D X440: ₹2,39,500

The ex-showroom prices for the Street Bob and the CVO models—CVO Street Glide and CVO Road Glide—will be announced closer to their official launch dates.

Honda Cars India Ltd. has launched the New City Sport, adding a sportier option to its mid-size sedan lineup!

-- Priced at ₹14,88,900 (ex-showroom, Delhi)

-- The New City Sport receives a bold makeover with blacked-out accents across key exterior elements. It features a black grille, a trunk lip spoiler, a shark fin antenna, and black ORVMs. The addition of multi-spoke grey alloy wheels further amplifies its sporty stance. Exclusive badging identifies the model, setting it apart in the City lineup.

-- Inside, the car adopts a dark theme with all-black interiors paired with red stitching accents on the seats, door panels, and steering wheel. Other enhancements include a black roof liner, plush soft-touch door inserts, and a red dash garnish, adding to the sporty atmosphere. A seven-color ambient lighting system enhances the cabin's visual appeal, providing a modern touch.

-- Powered by a 1.5L i-VTEC petrol engine compliant with E20 fuel standards. Delivering 121PS of power and 145NM of torque, it is paired with a CVT transmission featuring paddle shifters with a claimed mileage of 18.4 km/l.

--The New City Sport is available in limited units and three color options: Radiant Red Metallic, Platinum White Pearl, and Meteoroid Gray Metallic.

#HondaCitySport #NewLaunch #LimitedEdition #MidSizeSedan #AutomotiveNews

The iconic Harley-Davidson Fat Bob will no longer be part of the brand's lineup in India. Known for its bold design, wide tires, and powerful performance, the Fat Bob had a unique appeal among cruiser enthusiasts.

As part of the 2025 updates, Harley-Davidson has decided to streamline its offerings, making way for the reintroduction of models like the Street Bob while discontinuing the Fat Bob in the Indian market.

What are your thoughts on this move? Will you miss the Fat Bob on Indian roads? Let us know!

Many of you have been asking about the new FASTag Annual Pass, and here’s a detailed breakdown! 

With an avg toll cost reduced to just ₹15 per trip, this ₹3,000 pass is valid for one year or up to 200 toll crossings—whichever comes first.

🔹 Who can use it? 
Private non-commercial vehicles (cars, jeeps, vans).

🔹 Where is it valid? 
All National Highways across India 

🔹 How to activate? 
Via the Rajmarg Yatra App or NHAI and MoRTH websites.

Mercedes-Benz has launched the EQS 580 4MATIC 'Celebration Edition' in India, priced at ₹1.30 crore (ex-showroom) and limited to 50 units. This edition prioritizes rear-seat comfort with several enhancements.

The Rear Seat Comfort Package includes multi-contour seats with heating, neck and shoulder warmers, and massage functions offering both revitalizing and relaxing effects. The Executive Seats in the rear provide up to a 38-degree recline with an extended seat cushion for improved thigh support. The Chauffeur Package allows the front passenger seat to tilt forward, giving rear passengers extra legroom

Other premium touches include complete Nappa leather upholstery, illuminated designer belt buckles, and chrome accents 

The car also offers a range of 813 km (ARAI certified) from its 107.8 kWh battery, along with advanced tech features like MBUX augmented reality navigation and rear axle steering for better handling.
